,"County Limerick, Irland":"County Limerick, Ireland","Franciscan Friary, Ardfert, County Kerry, Ireland":"Ardfert, County Kerry, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]},{"name":"fitzMaurice","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Aidan, Ciaran, Colm.","Irish: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (see   Fitz  ) + the personal name <i>Maurice</i> (see   Morris   1), ‘son of <i>Maurice</i>’. This surname is common in Ireland, where it has also been Gaelicized as <b>Mac Muiris</b>. The Irish family of <i>Fitzmaurice</i> share a common Norman ancestry with the   Fitzgerald   family. They can be traced to Thomas <i>Fitzmaurice</i>, whose brother Gerald was the ancestor of the Irish Fitzgerald dynasty. Their father was Maurice Fitzgerald, a Norman baron (died 1176)."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["Either a short form of any of the numerous names representing a transferred use of a surname formed with the Anglo-Norman French prefix <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son of ’, as for example   Fitzgerald  ,   Fitzroy  , or a transferred use of the surname <i>Fitz</i>, which may be of the same derivation, but applied originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same given name, or a local name from Fitz in Shropshire, named with the Old English personal name <i>Fitt</i> + <i>hōh</i> ‘hill spur’."]},{"name":"Fitzmorris","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Fitzmaurice  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas fitzMaurice fitzThomas 1st Baron of Lixnaw and Kerry was born about 1220, his father, Maurice Fitz Thomas Fitzgerald, was 25 and his mother, Johanna FitzHenry, was 19. He had at least 1 son with Grainne MacMorrogh. He died on 20 January 1280, in County Limerick, Ireland, at the age of 61, and was buried in Ardfert, County Kerry, Ireland."},"et":{"ABT 1220–20 jan 1280":"umbes 1220–20. jaanuar 1280","1220–1280":"1220–1280","1220–Female":"1220–Surnud","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1260–1305":"1260–1305","1242–Female":"1242–Surnud","1197–1253":"1197–1253","1202–Female":"1202–Surnud","20 jan 1280":"20. jaanuar 1280","1242":"1242","1253":"1253","1220":"1220","1197":"1197","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","1305":"1305","about 1219":"umbes 1219","1225":"1225","ABT 1220":"umbes 1220","1202":"1202","about 1253":"umbes 1253","Desmond, Kerry, Munster, Ireland":"Diocese of Kerry, Munster, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Dungarvan, County Waterford, Ireland":"Dungarvan, County Waterford, Iirimaa","County Limerick, Irland":"County Limerick, Iirimaa","Franciscan Friary, Ardfert, County Kerry, Ireland":"Ardfert, County Kerry, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"ABT 1220–20 jan 1280":"noin 1220–20. tammikuuta 1280","1220–1280":"1220–1280","1220–Female":"1220–Kuollut","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1260–1305":"1260–1305","1242–Female":"1242–Kuollut","1197–1253":"1197–1253","1202–Female":"1202–Kuollut","20 jan 1280":"20. tammikuuta 1280","1242":"1242","1253":"1253","1220":"1220","1197":"1197","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","1305":"1305","about 1219":"noin 1219","1225":"1225","ABT 1220":"noin 1220","1202":"1202","about 1253":"noin 1253","Desmond, Kerry, Munster, Ireland":"Diocese of Kerry, Munster, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti","Dungarvan, County Waterford, Ireland":"Dungarvan, County Waterford, Irlanti","County Limerick, Irland":"County Limerick, Irlanti","Franciscan Friary, Ardfert, County Kerry, Ireland":"Ardfert, County Kerry, Irlanti"},"fr":{"ABT 1220–20 jan 128